{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Form control · Stisla v3{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Form control</h1>
    <p class="lead">A single class for every text-like form field — inputs, selects, textareas. The shape is identical across all three; the element decides the behavior.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.form-control</code> to any <code>&lt;input&gt;</code>. Pair with a <code>&lt;label&gt;</code> tied via <code>for</code>/<code>id</code> so the field is reachable. The same class works on <code>&lt;select&gt;</code> (see <a href="/select">/select</a>) and <code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code> below.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="basicInput" class="form-label">Email</label>
      <input type="email" class="form-control" id="basicInput" placeholder="you@example.com" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sizes</h2>
    <p>Heights are pinned at 28 / 36 / 44&nbsp;px to match the button scale.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="demo-stack" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <input type="text" class="form-control form-control--sm" placeholder="Small" />
      <input type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="Default" />
      <input type="text" class="form-control form-control--lg" placeholder="Large" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Textarea</h2>
    <p>The same class works on <code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code>. The min-height clamp drops so the <code>rows</code> attribute and content drive the height. The textarea handle is vertical-only — width tracks the parent.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="basicTextarea" class="form-label">Notes</label>
      <textarea class="form-control" id="basicTextarea" rows="3" placeholder="Anything else we should know?"></textarea>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Input types</h2>
    <p>The class applies to every text-like input: <code>text</code>, <code>email</code>, <code>password</code>, <code>number</code>, <code>search</code>, <code>tel</code>, <code>url</code>, <code>date</code>, <code>time</code>.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="demo-stack" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <input type="email" class="form-control" placeholder="email" />
      <input type="password" class="form-control" placeholder="password" value="hunter2" />
      <input type="number" class="form-control" placeholder="number" />
      <input type="search" class="form-control" placeholder="search" />
      <input type="date" class="form-control" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Helper text</h2>
    <p>Use <code>.form-text</code> below the input for short hints. Wire it to the input with <code>aria-describedby</code> so screen readers announce it.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="passwordInput" class="form-label">Password</label>
      <input type="password" class="form-control" id="passwordInput" aria-describedby="passwordHelp" />
      <div id="passwordHelp" class="form-text">At least 8 characters, one number.</div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Validation</h2>
    <p>Mark a field as invalid with <code>aria-invalid="true"</code>. Pair with <code>.form-text--error</code> tied via <code>aria-describedby</code> so the error reaches assistive tech. This is the canonical hook for server-rendered errors — Django, Rails, Laravel render the attribute, and the border + message paint themselves. Native validation (<code>required</code>, <code>type="email"</code>) also kicks in via <code>:user-invalid</code> after the user interacts.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="demo-stack" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <div>
        <label for="invalidEmail" class="form-label">Email</label>
        <input
          type="email"
          class="form-control"
          id="invalidEmail"
          value="not-an-email"
          aria-invalid="true"
          aria-describedby="invalidEmailError" />
        <div id="invalidEmailError" class="form-text form-text--error">Please enter a valid email address.</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <label for="nativeRequired" class="form-label">Required (try submitting empty)</label>
        <input type="email" class="form-control" id="nativeRequired" required placeholder="you@example.com" />
        <div class="form-text">Lights up red after a failed submit via <code>:user-invalid</code>.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Disabled &amp; readonly</h2>
    <p><code>disabled</code> blocks interaction and dims the field. <code>readonly</code> keeps the value reachable for copy but rejects edits — the bg shifts a tier to signal "selectable, not editable".</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="demo-stack" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <input type="text" class="form-control" value="Disabled" disabled />
      <input type="text" class="form-control" value="Readonly" readonly />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Plain text</h2>
    <p>Swap <code>.form-control</code> for <code>.form-control--plaintext</code> to render a readonly value as bare text — no border, no background, but it still aligns with neighboring inputs in a form row. Pair with <code>readonly</code> on the input.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="plainEmail" class="form-label">Email</label>
      <input type="email" readonly class="form-control--plaintext" id="plainEmail" value="you@example.com" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Color picker</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.form-control--color</code> to an <code>&lt;input type="color"&gt;</code>. The native swatch wears the field's inner radius (outer minus padding, V3.md §3.4) so the chip and the frame share a center.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="demo-row">
      <label for="brandColor" class="form-label" style="margin-bottom: 0;">Brand</label>
      <input type="color" class="form-control form-control--color" id="brandColor" value="#3b82f6" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>File input</h2>
    <p>The same class styles <code>type="file"</code>. The selector button stretches to the field's inner height and reads as the primary affordance; the filename trails after it.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <label for="fileInput" class="form-label">Upload</label>
      <input type="file" class="form-control" id="fileInput" />
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>
{% endblock %}
